Four people were recused after their boat capsized at the Tugela beach launch site on the KwaZulu-Natal north coast on Saturday morning. IPSS Medical Rescue paramedics and Search and Rescue division, responded to the Tugela launch site for reports of a boating accident, said IPSS spokesperson Paul Herbst. “Once on scene it was established that a ski-boat had capsized on the surf approximately 150m out to sea. Four occupants of the boat were hanging on to the life boat and they were rescued. Rescue crafts were launched and the stricken vessel was righted, before being towed to shore. No serious injuries were sustained. “Thank you to local fishermen who assisted and to the NSRI crew who were on a training exercise in the vicinity and responded.” 